# UI Quality Rules

## Text contrast
- NEVER use `text-[#6B7280]`, `text-[#9CA3AF]`, or any gray lighter than `#6B7280` on the app background `#F0F2F5`. These fall below 3:1 contrast and are invisible in practice.
- For body/subtitle text on `#F0F2F5` (page bg): use `text-[#4B5563]` minimum.
- For muted/caption text: use lighter grays ONLY inside `bg-white` cards, never directly on the page background.
- Rule of thumb: white card → `#9CA3AF` OK | page bg `#F0F2F5` → minimum `#4B5563`.

## Before every push
1. After changing text, grep the actual file to confirm the new value is present before saying "done".
2. When changing a color, verify the contrast of that color against its actual background.
3. Never claim a visual fix is done without confirming the change exists in the saved file.
